The paper deals with image clustering, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method involves unsupervised and transfer learning, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of handcrafted features, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with clustering, which is a common task in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
